<doc id="1035499" wikidata="Q629208" url="?curid=1035499" title="Truth or dare?">
<text>Truth or dare? is a mostly verbal party game requiring two or more players. Players are given the choice between answering a question truthfully, or performing a &quot;&quot;. The game is particularly popular among adolescents and children, and is sometimes used as a when gambling.

== History ==
The game has existed for hundreds of years, with at least one variant, &quot;questions and commands&quot;, being attested as early as 1712:

Truth or dare may ultimately derive from command games such as the ancient Greek basilinda (in Greek: βασιλίνδα). This game is described by Julius Pollux: &quot;in which we are told a king, elected by lot, commanded his comrades what they should perform&quot;.

== See also ==
* Game of dares
* Never have I ever

